The global home infusion therapy market is anticipated to show substantial growth by 2028, driven by several key segments within the industry. The product segment including infusion pumps, IV sets, IV cannulas, needleless connectors, elastomeric pumps, patient-controlled analgesia pumps, and implantable ports is expected to witness significant demand. In terms of application, the market is projected to experience growth in areas such as anti-infectives, endocrinology, hydration therapy, chemotherapy, enteral nutrition, parenteral nutrition, and specialty pharmaceuticals. Indications such as infectious diseases, diabetes, pain management, hematology, oncology, gastroenterology, and others will play a crucial role in shaping the market landscape. Furthermore, the distribution channels of hospitals, ambulatory surgical centers, and home care settings will also influence market growth across different regions.

